{
  "text": "Let's create a GitHub Actions workflow for Pulumi. The workflow runs on pull requests and pushes to main. It sets up Node.js, installs Pulumi CLI, and configures OSPredetions using GitHub Secrets. On pull requests, it runs Pulumi Preview to show what would change. On pushes to main, it runs Pulumi Preview to show what would change. On pushes to main, it runs Pulumi up to deploy. We use Pulumi Service Backend to store state, which enables team collaboration. The work rate is a great price. Thank you for watching.",
